JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi has turned down a nomination to the ANC's national executive committee (NEC). Lesufi says he’s humbled by the nomination. He hasn’t given any reasons for refusing to serve on the NEC but the decision sparked a flood of comments on his Facebook page. Some users are asking him to reconsider, saying the country needs strong, credible leadership now more than ever. eNCA